peter struck plato on divination as a form of cognition stanford department of classics skip to navigation department of classics standford university logo header home people programs courses projects news events resources contact peter struck plato on divination as a form of cognition tue 5 18 2010 5 00 6 30 pm classics department main quad building 110 stanford ca map this talk provides a look at divination in antiquity not as a social historical phenomenon used to consolidate public opinion by controlling divine authority nor as a paranormal practice guided by personal intervention from gods or spirits instead the philosophers approach it as a form of cognition as such divination looks like the result of a long and still ongoing human attempt to acculturate extra rational forms of knowledge akin to intuition rather than the result of exotic theological commitments login to post comments email stanford classics find us on facebook address & phone search upcoming events classics on screen clash of the titans 1981 with prof susan stephens 01 19 2012 martin devecka in praise of small creatures elephants beavers and juvenal's 12th satire 01 23 2012 see more recent news faculty grad student group awarded funding for shc research worshop 05 20 2011 stanford classics tops national research council rankings 09 28 2010 scit's production of aristophanes wasps in the spotlight 02 14 2011 see more news site info 2012 stanford university department of classics all rights reserved site design by chapter three login login with sunet speaker request webform for faculty stanford classics wikisite powered by drupal an open source content management system
